.TH update_bus_guide  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBupdate_bus_guide\fR \-  Updates the selected bus guide as specified
.SH Syntax \fBupdate_bus_guide\fR  [-help]   [-avoidObstacles]  [-layer_horizontal {<id> | <id1:id2>}]  [-layer_vertical {<id> | <id1:id2>}]   [-no_snap]  [-resize_direction {low high}]  [-type {hard | soft}]  [-width <value> | -net_group <name> | {{-rule <rulename> | {-wire_width <value> -wire_spacing <value>}} [-with_shield]}]
.P Updates the selected bus guide as specified. The bus guide can expand automatically with pre-route or routing blockage.
.P Use the update_bus_guide command when you need to modify the layer or width information of an existing bus guide. Before using the update_bus_guide command, select the bus guide with the selectBusGuide command. 
.SH Parameters   "\fB-help\fR" Prints a brief description that includes type and default information for each update_bus_guide parameter.  For a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use the man command:   man update_bus_guide  "\fB-avoidObstacles\fR" Specifies whether to avoid pre-routes and blockages (detour). If this option is not specified, the bus guide is expanded with the pre-route and routing blockage.  "\fB-layer_horizontal {<id> | <id1:id2>} \fR" Specifies the horizontal layer id or a layer range. Use this parameter to change the horizontal layer of the selected bus guide.   "\fB-layer_vertical {<id> | <id1:id2>}\fR" Specifies the vertical layer id or a layer range. Use this parameter to change the vertical layer of the selected bus guide.   "\fB-net_group <name>\fR" Specifies the net group name. The net group you specify must be an existing net group.   "\fB-no_snap\fR" Specifies whether or not to snap the bus guide.  "\fB-resize_direction {low high}\fR" Specifies the resize direction as follows:
.RS  "*" 2 low: Expands the selected bus guide from the top or right edge.   "*" 2 high: Expands the selected bus guide from the bottom or left edge. 
.RE   If this option is not specified, the bus guide is expanded from the center line.  "\fB-rule <rulename>\fR" Specifies the rule name or default. Use this parameter to change the selected bus guide width as per the wire width or wire spacing defined in the specified LEF rule. If <rulename> is not specified, default LEF rule is used.  Note: This parameter cannot be used with the -width, -wire_width, or wire_spacing parameters.  "\fB-type {hard | soft}\fR" Specifies the new constraint type of the bus guide:
.RS  "*" 2 hard - After running Early Global Route (eGR), NanoRoute (NR), or NanoRoute High Frequency Router (NRHF), the route obeys the path of the bus guide.  "*" 2 soft - After running eGR, NR, or NRHF, the bus guide only guides the route path. The tool can route the net out of the bus guide.
.RE   "\fB-width <value>\fR" Specifies bus guide width. Use this parameter to change the selected bus guide width to the specified value.  Note: This parameter cannot be used with the -rule, -wire_width, or wire_spacing parameters.  "\fB-wire_spacing <value>\fR" Specifies wire spacing. Use this parameter to change the selected bus guide width as per the specified wire spacing value.  Note: This parameter cannot be used with either the -rule parameter or the -width parameter.  "\fB-wire_width <value>\fR" Specifies wire width. Use this parameter to change the selected bus guide width as per the specified wire width value.  Note: This parameter cannot be used with either the -rule parameter or the -width parameter.  "\fB-with_shield\fR" Adds shield wire base on the shield net property defined by the following setEditMode options: -outer_shield_spacing, -outer_shield_width, and -shield. When specified with:
.RS  "*" 2 -wire_width and -wire_spacing, the tool considers only the outer shielding nets.  "*" 2 -rule, the tool considers the shielding nets between wires.
.RE 
.SH Example
.RS  "*" 2  The following command updates the width of the selected bus guide as per the NDR <doublewidth> defined in LEF. It also changes the horizontal layer of the selected bus guide to 3 and considers the shielding nets between wires.  update_bus_guide -rule doublewidth -layer_horizontal 3 -with_shield
.RE 
.SH Related Information
.RS  "*" 2 createBusGuide  "*" 2 deleteBusGuide  "*" 2 selectBusGuide  "*" 2 setEditMode  "*" 2 Bus Planning chapter in the User Guide  "*" 2 Edit Menu chapter in the Menu Reference
.RS  "*" 2 Bus Guide
.RE 
.RE
.P
